# Roadmap

This roadmap outlines the current development direction for BlueNovaAI.

---

## Short-Term Goals

### 1) Bug fixing and stability
- Resolve known UI/backend issues.
- Improve reliability of chat flow, state handling, and feature interactions.
- Reduce regressions while iterating on new features.

### 2) UI improvements
- Polish layout consistency and readability.
- Improve navigation clarity and editing ergonomics.
- Continue refining Help and creation workflows for faster iteration.

### 3) TTS implementation
- Add text-to-speech support for assistant outputs.
- Make playback practical for local usage.
- Integrate TTS controls into existing UI without disrupting current chat flow.

---

## Long-Term Goals

### 1) Image generation + interpretation support
- Add image generation capabilities.
- Add image understanding/interpretation workflows.
- Integrate visual input/output into chat and bot tools.

### 2) RAG + file operations support
- Add Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) features.
- Support reading, editing, and creating files as part of AI workflows.
- Build practical document/project-aware AI usage in one interface.

### 3) Custom Tool Creation module / MCP support
- Enable user-defined tool creation modules.
- Add MCP-compatible tooling integration.
- Expand BlueNovaAI into a flexible local AI orchestration platform.

---

## Guiding direction

BlueNovaAI continues toward the same core vision:
**an all-in-one localhost-optimized AI interface** that is practical, extensible, and production-ready for daily use.
